In your for loop, you are always assigning the last element of "items" list
list to variable 'total'. What you need is to add all the costs in a runnin
running total fashion.

Here's how it can be corrected:

val items = [
  { name: "a", cost: 2 },
  { name: "b", cost: 3 },
  { name: "c", cost: 4 }
];

var total = 0;
for(item in items) {
  total = total + item.cost;
}
print(total);
